        <h3><a href="https://www.gosh-community.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GOSH Community</a></h3>
        <p>Building a global network where hardware knowledge flows freely, centering equity and local agency in tool development.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="acknowledgement-card">
        <h3><a href="https://publiclab.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Public Lab</a></h3>
        <p>Pioneering community science with accessible tools for environmental monitoring and data sovereignty.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="acknowledgement-card">
        <h3><a href="https://www.appropedia.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Appropedia</a></h3>
        <p>Creating a living library of sustainable technology and collaborative problem-solving for communities worldwide.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="acknowledgement-card">
        <h3><a href="https://www.oshwa.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">OSHWA</a></h3>
        <p>Advocating for open source hardware principles and building infrastructure for collaborative innovation.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="acknowledgement-card">
        <h3><a href="https://farmhack.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Farm Hack</a></h3>
        <p>Empowering farmers as designers and innovators, sharing agricultural tools and knowledge in the commons.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="acknowledgement-card">
        <h3><a href="https://www.scienceforsociety.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Community Science</a></h3>
        <p>Movements globally that center local knowledge, consent-based research, and accountability to communities.</p>
      </article>

      <article class="acknowledgement-card">
        <h3><a href="https://creativecommons.org/science/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Creative Commons</a></h3>
        <p>Building legal infrastructure that lets knowledge flow freely while protecting creator rights and community interests.</p>
      </article>
    </div>

    <p class="acknowledgements-note">
      If you're working on similar open science or regenerative tech projects, <a href={formURL} target="_blank">let's connect</a>.
      We're stronger together.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- GETTING STARTED - 4 STEPS -->
  <section class="getting-started-section">
    <h2>Getting Started</h2>
    <p class="section-intro">New to Arc^ or plasma research? Here's how to begin:</p>
    
    <div class="getting-started-grid">
      <article class="start-card">
        <span class="process-number">01</span>
        <h3>Understand RE:TECH</h3>
        <p>Familiarize yourself with the principles and values that guide Arc^. Learn how we approach research, innovation, and collaboration differently ‚Äî open by default, safety first, and community-led.</p>
        <a href={withBase("/how")} class="button button-outline">Explore How We Work</a>
      </article>

      <article class="start-card">
        <span class="process-number">02</span>
        <h3>Start With Why</h3>
        <p>Read about why I started Arc^ and reflect on your own motivations. How would you approach this work? What perspectives do you bring? Arc^ grows through dialogue and diverse viewpoints.</p>
        <a href={withBase("/why")} class="button button-outline">Read My Story</a>
      </article>

      <article class="start-card">
        <span class="process-number">03</span>
        <h3>Find Your Entry Point</h3>
        <p>Explore active research areas and see where your interests align. Begin your own research, put together an experimental design, or find a project that matches your training. Even without formal protocols yet, understanding the vision helps us find the right fit together.</p>
        <a href={withBase("/projects")} class="button button-outline">Browse Projects</a>
      </article>

      <article class="start-card">
        <span class="process-number">04</span>
        <h3>Let's Connect</h3>
        <p>Contact me for guidance, to collaborate, or to help transform Arc^ by Ali into a collective global hub for change. No formal applications ‚Äî just authentic conversation about what you want to build.</p>
        <a href={formURL} target="_blank" class="button button-outline">Contact Ali</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

